    <h1>Gregory Vigo Torres</h1>
    <h3 class="italic">Spanish to English Translator &mdash; since 2008</h3>

    <main>
      <p>I’m a <strong>native English speaker</strong> from the United States, where I was born and raised. I’ve lived in Spain for more than 20 years.</p>

<p>In my 15 years of experience I’ve translated a wide range of texts, including various kinds of manuals, press releases, carbon footprint reports and numerous texts about art and tourism.
I’ve done jobs for coops, publishing houses, architecture firms, universities and many other kinds of companies and organizations.
I’m a specialist in <strong>general business translation</strong> and my specific areas of expertise are <strong>IT, art and tourism</strong>.</p>

<p>I have an MFA from the University of Pennsylvania and a BFA from The School of the Art Institute of Chicago.
I’m a member of Asetrad (no. 4038).</p>

<p>I mainly use OmegaT, Okapi/Rainbow, LibreOffice and MS Office.</p>

